    <item>
      <title>Chart: Most people think the justice system is fair, fewer say it&#39;s effective</title>
      <link>http://lesscrime.info/post/fairness-perception/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Sep 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://lesscrime.info/post/fairness-perception/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;script src=&#34;http://lesscrime.info/rmarkdown-libs/header-attrs/header-attrs.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Every month, the Crime Survey for England and Wales asks a representative sample of adults about their perceptions of the criminal justice system. Across age, education, ethnic and employment groups, most people believe the system as a whole is fair, but only about half say it is effective.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://lesscrime.info/post/fairness-perception_files/figure-html/display%20plot-1.png&#34; width=&#34;672&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../fairness-perception.png&#34;&gt;larger image&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/mpjashby/lesscrime.info/blob/master/content/post/fairness-perception.Rmd&#34;&gt;annotated R code to produce this chart&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data source: &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/crimeandjustice/datasets/perceptionscriminaljusticesystemcsewopendatatable&#34;&gt;Crime Survey for England and Wales, 2019&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
